description.narrative: The project's development objective is to increase the export competitiveness of Moldovan enterprises and decrease the regulatory burden they face. This PDO will be achieved through a set of measures that aim to: (i) improve the business environment through regulatory reforms that reduce the cost of doing business; (ii) help SMEs and exporters to get access to business development services;and (iii) improve access to medium and long term finance for export oriented enterprises.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Action Plan (FA) | Description :The Recipient, through the MOE, shall: (a) based on the result of activitiesunder Parts 1(a)(iii) and 1(b) of the Project, prepareand furnish to the Association no later than January 31, 2015, or such laterdate as the Association shall agree, an Action Plan satisfactory to the Association (including a timetable); and (c) implement saidAction Plan in accordance with its terms. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Credit Line Directorate (LA) | Description :The Borrower, through the MOF, shall maintain, throughout theProject implementation, the Credit Line Directorate (CLD), which shall be responsible for the day to day management andimplementation of Part 3(a) of the Project. The CLD shall be provided with adequate staff, funding, facilities and other resourcessatisfactory to the Bank and required for implementation of Part 3(a) of the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Environmental Management Framework (FA) | Description :The Recipient shall, and shall cause the Matching GrantBeneficiaries to, carry out Part 2(b)(ii) of the Project in accordance withthe EMF. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Environmental Management Framework (LA) | Description :The Borrower shall, and shall cause the Eligible PFIs tocarry out part 3(a) of the Project in accordance with the EMF. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Environmental Management Plan (FA) | Description :The Recipient shall, and shall cause each Matching GrantBeneficiary to, prior to carrying out any activities under Part 2(b) (ii) of the Project, prepare EMPs in accordance with the EMF,in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, and to implement said activities in accordance with the relevant EMP. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Environmental Management Plan (LA) | Description :The Borrower shall, and shall cause the Eligible PFIs to causethe Beneficiary Enterprises to, when applicable, prior to carrying out any Subproject under Part 3(a) of the Project, prepare EMPsin accordance with the EMF, in form and substance satisfactory to theBank, and to implement said Subproject in accordance with therelevant EMP. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Line of Credit Operational Manual (LA) | Description :The Borrower shall: (a) prepare and adopt a LOCOperational Manual under terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank, and (b) thereafter, carry out Part 3(a) of the Project inaccordance with the requirements set forth in the LOC Operational Manual, including eligibility criteria for Eligible PFIs andBeneficiary Enterprises, selection procedures and implementation conditions. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :MOE (FA and LA) | Description :For the purposes of the Project, the Recipient/Borrower, through the MOE, shallbe responsible for the overall implementation (including the financial management and procurement aspects) of the Project. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Matching Grant Agreement (FA) | Description :The Recipient, through the MOE, shall provide financing, on a grantbasis, to Matching Grant Beneficiaries pursuant to a standard agreement, in a format and substance acceptable to the Association,to be entered into between the Recipient and a Matching Grant Beneficiary. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Matching Grant Facility (FA) | Description :The Recipient, through the MOE, shall retain staff to administer theMatching Grant Facility (MGF) in numbers, with qualifications,experience and responsibilities acceptable to the Association and setforth in the Operational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Matching Grant Manual (FA) | Description :The Recipient shall: (a) prepare and adopt a Matching Grant Manualunder terms and conditions acceptable to the Association, and (b) thereafter, carry out Part 2(b)(ii) of the Project in accordancewith the requirements set forth in the Matching Grant Manual, including eligibility criteria, selection procedures andimplementation conditions. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Operational Manual (FA and LA) | Description :The Recipient/Borrower shall carry out the Project in accordancewith the requirements set forth in the Operational Manual and thisAgreement and shall not assign, amend, abrogate or waive anyprovision of the Operational Manual without prior approval of the Association. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :PIU (FA and LA) | Description :The Recipient/Borrower, through the MOE, shall maintain the PIU until completionof the Project with staff, resources and terms of reference acceptable to the Association/Bank and in accordance with theOperational Manual and shall assign to it responsibility foroverall daily management of the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Procurement Information (FA and LA) | Description :The Recipient/Borrower shall no later than October 31 ofevery year during the implementation of the Project, beginning on October 31, 2015 exchange views with the Association/Bank on theresults of the Procurement Progress Report completed for the Recipient/Borrower's previous calendar year and thereafter implementsuch recommended measures, as agreed with the Association/Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Procurement Report (FA and LA) | Description :The Recipient/Borrower shall, no later than September 30 of everyyear during the implementation of the Project, beginning on September 30, 2015, prepare and furnish to the Association aprocurementprogress report (Procurement Report), in form and substance acceptable to the Association/Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Safeguards (LA) | Description :Under Part 3(a) of the Project, the Borrower shall ensure that no investmentsinvolving the involuntary acquisition of land or the displacement of persons, or investments that involve the use or potentialpollution of international waterways or any other investment included in the negative list of investments included in the EMF, arefinanced with the proceeds of the Loan. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Selection of Matching Grant Beneficiaries (FA) | Description :Prior to the provision of the first two MatchingGrants, the Recipient shall obtain the Association's approval of the selection of the respective Matching Grant Beneficiaries. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Subsidiary Financing Agreement (LA) | Description :Prior to the implementation of any activity under Part 3(a)of the Project, the Borrower shall make part of the proceeds of the Loan available to each Eligible PFI under a SubsidiaryFinancing Agreement between the Borrower and the Eligible PFI, under terms and conditions acceptable to the Bank and set forth inthe LOC Operational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
